comment.author: 13935339@N05
comment._content: P-47D serial 42-27603 of the 378th Fighter Squadron, 362nd FG took a round through one of her propeller blades on a 9th AF ground support mission over the Continent on 31 August 1944. Less than two months later this ship was lost in a crash near Rouvres airfield on 18 October; LT Andrew J. Sunter was KIA in the bailout.
